Package realtimeweb.stickyweb.exceptions

Exception Summary
StickyWebCSVResponseParseException Thrown when the structure of the returned CSV data is incorrect.
StickyWebDataSourceNotFoundException Thrown when the given data source (i.e., the InputSteam) is not found.
StickyWebDataSourceParseException Thrown when the data source could not be parsed, usually because the JSON structure is incorrect.
StickyWebException The top-level, generic exception thrown by the Sticky Web library.
StickyWebInternetException Thrown when the internet cannot be accessed, typically because the network is down.
StickyWebInvalidPostArguments Thrown when the arguments for a Post call are invalid; most likely because an incorrect character encoding.
StickyWebInvalidQueryString Thrown when the Query String of a Get request is invalid, usually because of the URL or the parameters.
StickyWebJsonResponseParseException Thrown when the JSON response is from a call is invalid.
StickyWebLoadDataSourceException Thrown when the data source cannot be loaded; this might occur if the filestream is not valid.
StickyWebNotInCacheException The given query was not available in the cache.
StickyWebXMLResponseParseException Thrown when the XML data received is incorrect (possibly returned an HTML or Text formatted errors instead?).
